        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4799&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=the+%22necro%22+bug"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I would like to start out by saying that this bug happens to everyone, it's just that necromancers chose gear that makes this bug much more likely =)</P><P>------------------------------</P><P>You are fighting and get an add. No problem, root the add and continue fighting. </P><P>*resist* </P><P>Cast root again. </P><P>*resist* </P><P>Cast Feign Death.</P><P>"You have fallen to the ground"</P><P>The monster is on you now, and hitting hard.</P><P>Not wanting to take any chances, you zone.</P><P>When you come out the other side you have no buffs, and more HP than you had going in.</P><P>"sigh"</P><P>You rebuff, and zone back in.</P><P>---------------------------------</P><P>I'm sure everyone of us has been in that situation many times. Loseing all buffs when zoneing is a common thing for me, And I assume all necromancers experance this often.</P><P>Because of the nature of the bug it happens a lot more to necros than any other class. When you zone the server places you into the new zone. When placeing you there it checks your health, and if your health is less than 1 it kills you. </P><P>The problem is that you health is checked before your HP items are added to your health. The server thinks that you are dead, but as it finishes placeing you in the new zone it adds in your HP gear. The net result is that the server places you at 0 health, strips all buffs because you are dead. Then it finishes loading your information and adds the HP gear to your health. If you have 500hp in gear and zone with 300 life you will end up with no buffs and 500hp.</P><P>That is why I call this the "necro bug" A well equiped necro can easily double his health in equipment. Even worse we dont mind being low on health because of out taps and lich. </P><P>If I zone with half life I lose all buffs.</P><P>This is a very rare thing with all my other characters. After all even a warrior who loves HP gear as much as we do has a much larger base hp. Because that he will need to be at much less that half life for this to happen to him.</P><P>Normally this bug isnt a big deal at all. You may need to spend a few min more medding than normal. But it often will give you enought health to allow you to lich the mana for buffing without any problems. The only time I can think of that I have died from this bug is when I went AFK while zoneing into Kedge Keep and had DMF stripped.</P><P></P><P>This isnt a bad bug as far as bugs go =)</P><P><BR>I'm bringing this up for 2 reasons.</P><P>One reason is to let the youngsters know why they sometimes lose buffs when they zone.</P><P>The other is to find out if the necros with 4k-5k health actually find it a useful bug because if they are every low on mana and health one zone would give them enough health to lich the mana to start the "engine" again. =)</P><P>Laeelin (at 2am, so please fogive me if this is not understandable)</P><P><img src="http://www.butterflygifts.net/everquest/laeelinsmithing.gif" border=0></font></td>

